metadata.name: Bad Habits #26
metadata.description:
Get into Bad Habits...
  
Bad Habits is a collaboration project between me and evilnft.

This is a lottery style png layers project with generated background and layout.  

(illustrations by me / code by evilnft)

 - 20 illustrations
 - 10 text banners
- 8 layouts
- 2 layout styles : sketchy, blocks 
- 5 background colors  : eggshell, cheap pink, cheap craft, zancan, b&w
- 4 overall styles : tough luck, pink dreams, the zancan, black & white     

Twitter : twitter.com/Bad__Habits_
 Objkt : objkt.com/profile/badhabits/created  

Twitter : twitter.com/evilnft 
Objkt : https://objkt.com/profile/evilnft/created 

note from evilnft : just like my first project, my part of the proceeds from the primary sales of this project will also be used for donations.

metadata.name: Action Fields #40
metadata.description:
A generative painting based on abstract expressionism and the action paintings of Jackson Pollock.

Several different flow fields are used to create paths which are then painted in one of four different styles (pastel, paint, Pollock, black+gold). Additional features affect the background, path length + angles, level of detail, and mess (drips and splats). 

NOTES: 
- Some variations of the Pollock style may appear slightly different between browsers, but will render consistently in the same browser. 
- On slower devices, it may take some time to being drawing due to the background rendering.
- If you get a browser warning that the page is taking a long time, press continue.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 1200x928px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a variation of your edition at a resolution from 300 to 5,000 px. The ideal higher resolution is 2,000px.

metadata.name: a fleeting moment #31
metadata.description:
Abstract expressionism always has been, and always will be, my first love. With this piece, the initial premise was "can I write a bit of code that will render images in the style that I actually paint in real life?" 

It took several full days of poking and prodding, and I departed from the original mission once I had what I was looking for, but in general, I think I succeeded. My wife was looking over my shoulder at one point, and thought I was looking at a scan of one of my actual paintings, which sounds like success to me. 

Created with love in p5.js
